  "response_text": "Here is a healthy, realistic weekly meal plan designed for a busy college student with a strict **20-minute cooking time** per day.\n\n**The Core Philosophy:**\n- **Batch Cook (Sunday):** You will spend about 1 hour on Sunday prepping ingredients. This is the secret to 20-minute weekdays.\n- **No Waste:** Ingredients are reused across multiple meals (e.g., a bag of spinach, a rotisserie chicken).\n- **Minimal Dishes:** Most meals are one-pan, one-pot, or no-cook.\n- **Fuel for Brain & Body:** High in protein, fiber, and healthy fats to keep you full and focused.\n\n**Equipment Needed:**\n- Microwave\n- Non-stick skillet or frying pan\n- Sheet pan (for baking)\n- Cutting board & knife\n- Can opener\n\n**Sunday Meal Prep (1 hour):**\n1.  Cook 1 cup of **brown rice** or **quinoa** (makes ~3 cups).\n2.  Pick the meat off **1 rotisserie chicken** (buy pre-cooked). Shred it.\n3.  Wash and chop **bell peppers**, **onion**, and **broccoli**.\n4.  Make a batch of **vinaigrette dressing** (3 tbsp olive oil, 1 tbsp vinegar, salt, pepper).\n5.  Hard-boil 4-6 eggs.\n\n---\n\n### The Weekly Meal Plan\n\n| Day | Breakfast (5 min) | Lunch (10 min / no cook) | Dinner (20 min cook) | Snack Idea |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Mon** | Greek yogurt + granola + berries | **Chicken Salad Wraps**: Rotisserie chicken + Greek yogurt + grapes + whole wheat tortilla. | **Sheet Pan Salmon & Veggies**: Salmon fillet + broccoli + olive oil. Bake at 400°F for 15 min. | Apple + peanut butter |\n| **Tue** | Hard-boiled egg + banana | **Leftover Salmon & Veggies** over pre-cooked rice. | **15-Minute Black Bean Quesadillas**: Canned black beans + cheese + salsa in a skillet. Serve with avocado. | Handful of almonds |\n| **Wed** | Oatmeal (instant) + blueberries | **Leftover Quesadilla**. | **One-Pan Chicken & Veggies**: Pre-cooked chicken + pre-chopped bell peppers + pre-cooked rice + soy sauce. Stir-fry 5 min. | Greek yogurt |\n| **Thu** | Smoothie (banana + spinach + milk + peanut butter) | **Tuna Salad Crackers**: Canned tuna + mayo + crackers + baby carrots. | **Microwave \"Baked\" Potato & Beans**: Microwave potato (5 min). Top with canned chili beans, cheese, and sour cream. | Hard-boiled egg |\n| **Fri** | Greek yogurt + granola | **Leftover Chicken & Rice** (from Wed). | **20-Minute \"Pantry\" Pasta**: Cook pasta. While it boils, sauté garlic + canned tomatoes + spinach. Mix together. Top with parmesan. | Dark chocolate square |\n| **Sat** | Scrambled eggs (2 eggs + spinach) | **Deconstructed Burrito Bowl**: Pre-cooked rice + canned corn + black beans + salsa + avocado. | **\"Fancy\" Ramen**: Instant ramen (discard flavor packet). Add soy sauce, soft-boiled egg, frozen edamame, and sriracha. | Cottage cheese + fruit |\n| **Sun** | Smoothie | **Leftover Pasta**. | **Crustless Quiche**: Whisk 4 eggs + milk + leftover rotisserie chicken + frozen spinach. Bake in a skillet at 375°F for 18 min. | Popcorn |\n\n---\n\n### Grocery Shopping List (for the week)\n\n**Produce:**\n- Bananas (bunch)\n- Berries (fresh or frozen)\n- Apples\n- Avocados (2-3)\n- Spinach (1 bag)\n- Broccoli (1 head)\n- Bell peppers (2, any color)\n- Onion (1)\n- Garlic (1 head)\n- Lemons or limes (2)\n- Baby carrots (1 bag)\n- Potatoes (2 large baking potatoes)\n- Fresh or frozen edamame\n\n**Protein & Dairy:**\n- Rotisserie chicken (1 large)\n- Salmon fillet (1, ~6 oz)\n- Eggs (1 dozen)\n- Greek yogurt (plain, large tub)\n- Milk or plant-based milk\n- Cheese (shredded cheddar or Mexican blend)\n- Parmesan cheese (grated)\n- Canned tuna (1 can)\n- Canned black beans (2 cans)\n- Canned chili beans (1 can)\n\n**Pantry & Frozen:**\n- Brown rice or quinoa (1 bag)\n- Oats (1 container)\n- Granola (1 bag)\n- Whole wheat tortillas (1 pack)\n- Pasta (1 box, penne or spaghetti)\n- Instant ramen (1 pack, no seasoning)\n- Canned diced tomatoes (1 can)\n- Salsa (1 jar)\n- Olive oil\n- Vinegar (balsamic or apple cider)\n- Soy sauce (low sodium)\n- Peanut butter\n- Almonds or mixed nuts\n- Popcorn kernels or bagged popcorn\n- Dark chocolate (1 bar)\n- Frozen corn (1 bag)\n\n### Tips for Success:\n- **Use your microwave:** It's your best friend for steaming veggies (3 min) or reheating rice.\n- **Don't skip prep:** The Sunday hour saves you 30+ minutes every single day.\n- **Keep it simple:** It's okay to eat the same lunch twice. Variety comes from dinner.\n- **Hydrate:** Keep a water bottle at your desk. Dehydration causes fatigue and cravings.",
